From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Toon Verwaest <verwaest@chromium.org>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 13:49:11 +0200
Subject: [interpreter] Elide unreachable catch blocks and consider
 JumpIfToBoolean safe

In resumable functions, dead code processing might encounter catch
blocks with missing scope info if the try block cannot throw.
This CL elides unreachable catch blocks in Ignition, avoiding
generating handler table entries and bytecode for them.

To enable this for empty try blocks that contain implicit jumps
with type coercion, this CL also updates IsJumpWithoutEffects to
include JumpIfToBoolean bytecodes, as they do not have external
side effects or throw exceptions.

This avoids crashes in Maglev's PrewalkBytecode due to missing
scope info, and also avoids the DCHECK failure in BuildMergeStates.

